summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 35734 entitled: "An ordinance providing for the manner of advertising and receiving bids for bonds of the City of Seattle in the sum of Three Hundred Seventy Thousand Dollars ($370,000) of bonds of an issue of Five Hundred Forty-five Thousand Dollars ($545,000) voted at an election held in said city, March 2, 1915, under and pursuant to Ordinance No. 34220", approved February 10, 1916.
